    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-08-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-08-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">No. 140.</note>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Davis</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bancroft</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. <hi rend="smallcaps">226.]</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic"> Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-08-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 25, 1870.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I inclose herewith, for your information,
                            a copy of a dispatch of the 11th instant, No. 251, and of its
                            accompaniments, from Mr. Washburne, relative to a certificate of
                            protection desired by German residents in France.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. C. B. DAVIS.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>[For this inclosure see, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, “France,” Mr.
                                Washburne’s dispatch No. 251, dated August 11, 1870.]</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
